## 🚀 DEVELOPMENT WORKFLOW

### 1. Before Writing Code
- [ ] Check if schema exists in `@imbobi/schemas`
- [ ] Read `ARCHITECTURE_RESILIENCE_API_FIRST.md` for patterns
- [ ] Plan API endpoint in OpenAPI format
- [ ] Design component/service in isolation

### 2. Writing Code
- [ ] Use TypeScript (no `any`)
- [ ] Follow monorepo package isolation
- [ ] Implement resilience patterns (circuit breaker, retry)
- [ ] Add structured logging
- [ ] Handle errors explicitly

### 3. Before Committing
- [ ] Run `pnpm type-check` (0 errors required)
- [ ] Run `pnpm lint` (0 errors, acceptable warnings)
- [ ] Test locally: `pnpm dev`
- [ ] Update OpenAPI spec if API changed
- [ ] Update CLAUDE.md if architecture changed

