## 🔄 RESILIENCE PATTERNS

### Circuit Breaker
```typescript
// For external API calls that might fail
const circuitBreaker = new CircuitBreaker({
  failureThreshold: 5,        // Fail after 5 errors
  resetTimeout: 60000,        // Wait 1 min before retrying
  monitorInterval: 10000,
});

await circuitBreaker.execute(() =>
  externalService.call()
);
```

### Retry with Exponential Backoff
```typescript
// For transient failures (network timeouts, etc)
const retry = new RetryPolicy({
  maxAttempts: 3,
  initialDelayMs: 100,
  maxDelayMs: 5000,
  multiplier: 2,
});

await retry.execute(() => database.query());
```

### Timeout
```typescript
// Always set timeouts
return Promise.race([
  externalService.call(),
  new Promise((_, reject) =>
    setTimeout(() => reject(new TimeoutError()), 5000)
  ),
]);
```

### Bulkhead (Resource Isolation)
```typescript
// Separate queues by criticality
BullModule.registerQueue(
  { name: 'kyc-approval', defaultJobOptions: { attempts: 3 } },      // Critical
  { name: 'etapa-liberacao', defaultJobOptions: { attempts: 5 } },    // Critical
  { name: 'notification', defaultJobOptions: { attempts: 1 } },       // Non-critical
);
```

